      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Opportunity: we have had success in downloading the SVG from an algorithmic graphviz diagram and copying it into an HTML plugin as a way of freezing an interesting moment in the dynamic diagram."
    },
    {
      "id": "f7ec000",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Annoyance: when we make this move—freezing an interesting SVG via the HTML plugin—we loose the handy toolbar that lets us zoom in."
    },
    {
      "id": "5fcf8000",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Annoyance: the graphviz toolbar allows the download of the SVG, but does not allow the download of the DOT. Authors must perform some gymnastics to get the dot for use with external editors. But two download tools would need to be visually distinct—would clutter the scarce screen real estate available in the toolbar and would increase the cognitive load on the authors and readers in operating the tools."
