      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Brainstorm: the thought which inspired this page is to construct a custom element for use with the HTML plugin that allows an author to wrap their SVG diagram with something that can communicate with the wiki client to invoke the zoom behavior. Wouldn't have to be a custom element. Could also just be some convention we look for in the markup: a class or custom attribute to indicate this thing should be zoomable."
    },
    {
      "id": "72de000",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "But the notion of custom element and communications with wiki client call to mind the frame plugin. We sense an opportunity to build something like the frame.js library along with a companion wiki toolbar for the frame plugin that make use of this interesting boundary in the wiki client."
